Earlier today I attempted to post an IGTV video for Marvel but I posted it in Reels and then the regular post was cut short and the whole thing was a debacle. I appreciate the comments telling me I was bad at Instagram and thank my colleagues and executives for the many texts.

Here is a photo of me at a Murder Mystery Party a couple years ago. I would appreciate my privacy at this time.

node.text:
So a big inspiration of mine is @theandregregory and he has a new memoir called This is Not My Memoir and I think you should read it. When I was a kid his film with Wallace Shawn “My Dinner with Andre” -just based on the poster - looked like the most boring thing to ever exist. It fascinated me by how boring it looked. Well I was a kid, and years later I saw it and it’s an excellent daring film. Andre Gregory takes so many chances in theater and film and is so dedicated to what he wants to create that you’d think he didn’t understand how money works. I can’t overstate how much his creative passion for creative passion has inspired me. The book is just really good too. Well written etc. 
P.S. Kids will still find My Dinner with Andre boring but it’s neither their nor the film’s fault.

node.text: This was my favorite of @maryellenmatthewsnyc wonderful photos. That hat belonged to Hal Willner. He wore it almost every day. He was a brilliant music producer and artist and person. This was the first week I was ever at SNL without him and I felt it the whole week.

node.text: At 1 am, when the night couldn’t possibly get any better, Julian gave me his trench that he wore onstage and I acted like I wasn’t crying.

node.text:
Thank you @nbcsnl for going to every length so that we could put on a show safely and people could come and safely see it. 

I think this was the most magical episode I have been a part of. 

I love that place, in sickness and in health.
